<subSubSection id="4FFD6520FFBDFFEBD0ECFE797BF1FCCD" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph id="075836ABFFBDFFEBD0ECFE797A79FD11" blockId="3.[151,1437,450,1053]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFBDFFEBD0ECFE7979C7FDA5" bold="true" box="[199,463,487,513]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">External morphology.</emphasis>
Body dark brownish-red. Crown (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFBDFFEBD370FE797BBBFDA5" box="[859,947,487,513]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[184,1402,181,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[174,1413,174,1913]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Balala fulviventris (Walker, 1851), Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Head and thorax, lateral view; C. Face; D. Pygofer, lateral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635580" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635580/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) anterior margin round, length moderately shorter than 1/2 width between eyes. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFBDFFEBD468FD957CC2FD81" box="[1091,1226,523,549]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[184,1402,181,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[174,1413,174,1913]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Balala fulviventris (Walker, 1851), Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Head and thorax, lateral view; C. Face; D. Pygofer, lateral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635580" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635580/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Figs. 1A, B</figureCitation>
) reaching apex of clavus, exposed part of mesonotum about 1/7 scutellum long, scutellum moderately swollen and gradually declining toward apex, median longitudinal ridge very strong and extended through entire scutellum. Forewing with one transparent band present between apical cells and appendix. Hind femur with 5 macrosetae at apex, tibia with ca. 10, 10 setae in rows AD, PD, respectively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="075836ABFFBDFFEBD0ECFD217BF1FCCD" blockId="3.[151,1437,450,1053]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFBDFFEBD0ECFD217970FD7D" bold="true" box="[199,376,702,729]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFBDFFEBD1CFFD217A23FD7D" box="[484,555,703,729]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[184,1402,181,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[174,1413,174,1913]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Balala fulviventris (Walker, 1851), Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Head and thorax, lateral view; C. Face; D. Pygofer, lateral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635580" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635580/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
D–F) with dorsal inner margin nearly straight, pair of strong acute teeth present on subapex of ventral margin, pointing to each other; ventral appendage with base not very broad, reaching apex of pygofer, terminal slightly curved backward. Subgenital plate nearly as long as pygofer side. Apical margin (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFBDFFEBD564FC9978C6FCE1" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[184,1402,181,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[174,1413,174,1913]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Balala fulviventris (Walker, 1851), Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Head and thorax, lateral view; C. Face; D. Pygofer, lateral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635580" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635580/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Figs. 1 G, H</figureCitation>
) of connective slightly wavy; style about 1.5x connective long; aedeagus shaft tubular without any accessory, preatrium about as long as shaft, gonopore subapical on shaft ventral surface.
</paragraph>
